msgid "Name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:16
msgid ""
"GPIO_GET_LINEEVENT_IOCTL - Request a line with edge detection from the "
"kernel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:19
msgid "Synopsis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:23
msgid ""
"``int ioctl(int chip_fd, GPIO_GET_LINEEVENT_IOCTL, struct gpioevent_request "
"*request)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:26
msgid "Arguments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:28
msgid "``chip_fd``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:29
msgid "The file descriptor of the GPIO character device returned by `open()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:31
msgid "``request``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:32
msgid ""
"The :c:type:`event_request<gpioevent_request>` specifying the line to "
"request and its configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:36
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:38
msgid "Request a line with edge detection from the kernel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:40
msgid ""
"On success, the requesting process is granted exclusive access to the line "
"value and may receive events when edges are detected on the line, as "
"described in gpio-lineevent-data-read.rst."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:44
msgid ""
"The state of a line is guaranteed to remain as requested until the returned "
"file descriptor is closed. Once the file descriptor is closed, the state of "
"the line becomes uncontrolled from the userspace perspective, and may revert "
"to its default state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:49
msgid "Requesting a line already in use is an error (**EBUSY**)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:51
msgid ""
"Requesting edge detection on a line that does not support interrupts is an "
"error (**ENXIO**)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:54
msgid ""
"As with the :ref:`line handle<gpio-get-linehandle-config-support>`, the bias "
"configuration is best effort."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:57
msgid "Closing the ``chip_fd`` has no effect on existing line events."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:60
msgid "Configuration Rules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:62
msgid "The following configuration rules apply:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:64
msgid ""
"The line event is requested as an input, so no flags specific to output "
"lines, ``GPIOHANDLE_REQUEST_OUTPUT``, ``GPIOHANDLE_REQUEST_OPEN_DRAIN``, or "
"``GPIOHANDLE_REQUEST_OPEN_SOURCE``, may be set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:68
msgid ""
"Only one bias flag, ``GPIOHANDLE_REQUEST_BIAS_xxx``, may be set. If no bias "
"flags are set then the bias configuration is not changed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:71
msgid ""
"The edge flags, ``GPIOEVENT_REQUEST_RISING_EDGE`` and "
"``GPIOEVENT_REQUEST_FALLING_EDGE``, may be combined to detect both rising "
"and falling edges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:75
msgid "Requesting an invalid configuration is an error (**EINVAL**)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:78
msgid "Return Value"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:80
msgid ""
"On success 0 and the :c:type:`request.fd<gpioevent_request>` contains the "
"file descriptor for the request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/gpio/gpio-get-lineevent-ioctl.rst:83
msgid ""
"On error -1 and the ``errno`` variable is set appropriately. Common error "
"codes are described in error-codes.rst."
msgstr ""
